cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with location privacy preservation in wireless cognitive networks, which involves security and networking aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DB (Databases). The paper also proposes the use of probabilistic data structures, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and the performance evaluation of the proposed schemes, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
